  "time_ut": 1656345589,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba \u0daf\u0da9\u0db8\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0d86\u0dba\u0dad\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dad \u0dad\u0db6\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Crisis is being manipulated and institutions are being manipulated\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Jathika Nidahas Peramuna leader Wimal Weerawansa has said that the rulers are using the crisis in the country to get their hands on companies such as the Petroleum Corporation.",
        "Mr. Weerawansa said that instead of taking the crisis situation in the country to a revival, they are trying to take what is left and move from crisis to crisis, adding that the current situation should be changed by replacing the current Kaskibal regime with an all party government.",
        "Wimal Weerawansa stated this addressing a media briefing held at the party headquarters today (27).",
        "The statement made by the Minister in charge of the subject Kanchana Wijesekera that the filling stations owned by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation have to be handed over to the companies producing the oil should be closed down. He also said that it was a mistake.",
        "Mr. Weerawansa said that if the cause of the crisis was the responsibility of distributing oil to a state-owned company, there should be filling stations or fuel owned by the Indian Oil Company.",
        "He said that if such a statement had been made on another occasion, the employees of the Petroleum Corporation would have taken to the streets, adding that the authorities were using the disaster to put their hands where they could not touch under normal circumstances.",
        "He also said that the hopes of the party when Ranil Wickremesinghe became the Prime Minister have been completely dashed and he could not allow the country to move forward without a trustee.",
        "He said that in the event of a power cut of about 10 hours in the future, the government could not supply electricity alone and could give it to an Indian company.",
        "He said government ministers and MPs were taking advantage of the crisis and dragging the country hostage to India, adding that it was dangerous to continue to hand over power to those who were in the mood to sell national resources to plunder and make Sri Lanka the 29th state in India."
      ],
